From Joe Staudt Subject Re Trading in a car that's not paid Please In article Rhonda Gaines writes I'm planning on purchasing a new car and will be trading in my ' Mazda MX I've still got more years to pay on How does that get taken into account when I purchase my new car Does the dealership pay off my car and add on the amount they had to pay to the purchase price of the new car someone please explain this to If you don't already know it you should call the bank credit union finance company that holds the loan on your present car and get the current payoff If you are trading in your current car on the new car subtract the payoff amount from the trade in the dealer is giving If this turns out to be a negative number you need to reconsider the Subtract this difference from the price of the new This is the size of the loan you will need for the new The dealer will take care of paying off the loan on your old car out of the money you give them when you pick up your new At least that's how it worked for me years ago in thanks rhonda Joseph Staudt Telxon Box Usenet is like Tetris for people who still Akron OH remember how to Heller